              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Depends on how you define CLI. We tend to think of CLIs (and even TUIs) as requiring a terminal. But if we notice that modern terminals are all implemented atop a canvas of pixels, then arguably everything I build is a CLI. Some examples:\n"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_list",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "rich_text_section",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "link",
                    "url": "https://git.sr.ht/~akkartik/driver.love"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is my current favorite REPL."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "rich_text_section",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "link",
                    "url": "https://archive.org/details/akkartik-pensieve-2022-08-29"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is a less general CLI for browsing a set of text files using a command palette rather than a scrolling session of commands and responses."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ],
            "style": "bullet",
            "indent": 0,
            "border": 0
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "It seems like you can get all the behaviors we tend to look for in CLIs with very little code if we give up various intermediate levels of abstraction and just go back to drawing text on a canvas of pixels."
